SIMPLE: disputation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disputation
<hw>Dis`pu*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>desputeson</ets>, <ets>disputacion</ets>, OF.
<ets>desputeison</ets>, F. <ets>disputation</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>disputatio</ets>. See <er>Dispute</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of disputing; a reasoning or argumentation in
opposition to something, or on opposite sides; controversy in words;
verbal contest respecting the truth of some fact, opinion, proposition,
or argument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rhetorical exercise in which parties reason in
opposition to each other on some question proposed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disputatious</ent>⟦br⟧
